  <div class="grid-twocol">
    <h2>Scoping</h2>
    <div>
      <p>
        The solution is made in consideration to the "Four Essential Pillars for
        Supporting Ageing in the Right Place", authored by the Canadian National
        Institute of Aging, with a particular focus on pillar 4 - improving
        social connections to reduce loneliness & social isolation.
      </p>
      <br />
    </div>
  </div>
  <div>
    <img
      style="border-style: none; width: 80%;"
      src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dbiwj2oo8/image/upload/v1709584835/Frame_299_roqfla.svg"
    />
  </div>
  <div class="grid-twocol">
    <div></div>
    <p>
      This decision was made from my team and I's awareness that the idea of
      'caring for seniors' is accompanied by nuanced implications of medical
      care and invasion of privacy. We agree with this notion, and the idea that
      a service like Carriers That Care could unfairly put letter carriers in a
      position of authority without the proper training for it, thus putting
      seniors in a vulnerable position.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="grid-twocol">
    <div></div>
    <p>
      Our intention with introducing this framework is to ensure that we
      properly establish that we are designing around a domain within senior
      support that postal workers can reasonably intervene with, without
      reducing credibility or trust in Carriers that Care.
    </p>
  </div>

