  <div class="grid-twocol">
    <h2>Pre-visit</h2>
    <div>
      <h3>Defining the service</h3>
      <p>
        A web portal, accessible from Canada Post's pre-existing website, would
        describe the details of Carriers That Care, allowing for a shared
        understanding of the service between families and seniors. To ensure
        that contents of this website are also available offline, we have
        designed a brochure to be mailed to indicate from one party to the other
        their interest in the service.
      </p>
      <img src="/Landing Page Scrollthrough.gif" />
      <br />
      <br />
      <h3>Setting expectations & Consent</h3>
      <p>
        The sign-up process places emphasis on ensuring that the senior, who
        will be the recipient of the service, is aware of Carriers that Care and
        is consenting to receiving the service. Anticipating cases where
        families will be signing up on the senior's behalf, we have included
        callouts throughout the process, and will not begin delivery of the
        service until Canada Post receives vocal consent from the recipient.
      </p>
